---
layout: page.njk
title: Boards & Committees
subtitle: Aberdeen's citizen boards, commissions, and advisory committees.
description: City of Aberdeen boards, commissions, and advisory committees — meeting schedules, membership, and how to get involved.
breadcrumb:
  - label: Boards
---

<div class="space-y-10">

  <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">Aberdeen's boards and committees are composed of volunteer residents who advise the City Council and carry out important functions in planning, elections, ethics, economic development, and community preservation. All meetings are open to the public.</p>

  <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
    {% set boardList = [
      { name: "Aberdeen Parks & Recreation", url: "/boards/parks-recreation/", desc: "Manages parks, the Activity Center, and recreation programs for all residents.", phone: "(410) 272-1600" },
      { name: "Architectural Review Committee", url: "/boards/architectural-review/", desc: "Reviews proposed exterior changes to structures within designated historic areas.", phone: "(410) 272-1600" },
      { name: "Board of Appeals", url: "/boards/board-of-appeals/", desc: "Hears and decides zoning variances, special exceptions, and appeals of administrative decisions.", phone: "(410) 272-1600" },
      { name: "Board of Elections", url: "/boards/board-of-elections/", desc: "Administers Aberdeen municipal elections and oversees the voter registration process.", phone: "(410) 272-1600 ext. 211" },
      { name: "Economic Development Commission", url: "/boards/economic-development-commission/", desc: "Advises the City Council on strategies to attract, retain, and grow businesses in Aberdeen.", phone: "(410) 272-1600 ext. 216" },
      { name: "Ethics Commission", url: "/boards/ethics-commission/", desc: "Oversees compliance with the City's Ethics ordinance and reviews conflicts of interest.", phone: "(410) 272-1600" },
      { name: "Planning Commission", url: "/boards/planning-commission/", desc: "Reviews and makes recommendations on subdivision plans, zoning amendments, and development applications.", phone: "(410) 272-1600 ext. 221" },
      { name: "Heritage Trust Committee", url: "/boards/heritage-trust/", desc: "Preserves and promotes Aberdeen's historic resources, cultural heritage, and community memory.", phone: "(410) 272-1600" }
    ] %}
    {% for board in boardList %}
    <a href="{{ board.url | url }}" class="flex flex-col bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:border-gov-blue hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-200 group">
      <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-slate-100 flex items-center justify-center mb-3 group-hover:bg-gov-blue transition-colors duration-200" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-slate-500 group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path d="M13 6a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zM18 8a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM14 15a4 4 0 00-8 0v3h8v-3zM6 8a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM16 18v-3a5.972 5.972 0 00-.75-2.906A3.005 3.005 0 0119 15v3h-3zM4.75 12.094A5.973 5.973 0 004 15v3H1v-3a3 3 0 013.75-2.906z"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-navy mb-2 group-hover:text-gov-blue transition-colors duration-200 leading-snug">{{ board.name }}</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-slate-600 leading-relaxed flex-1">{{ board.desc }}</p>
      <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-slate-100">{{ board.phone }}</div>
    </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gov-blue-light rounded-xl p-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-2">Interested in Serving on a Board?</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mb-5">Aberdeen residents are encouraged to apply for vacancies on City boards and committees. Contact City Hall to learn about current openings.</p>
    <a href="{{ '/contact/' | url }}" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-gov-blue text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded hover:bg-gov-blue-dark transition-colors duration-200 text-sm">Contact City Hall</a>
  </div>

</div>
